# Hoax.ai Publisher Rules

The publisher is **blocked** until Publisher Dry-Run Harness (future sprint). Content Quality Standard (Sprint 14) is defined but does not authorize drafts or publishing.

## Absolute prohibitions

- No drafts in Sprint 13B control-plane work
- No public routes, sitemap expansion, or direct publishing
- No invented sources or claims
- No low-quality, keyword-only, or generic AI page generation
- No public classifier, tool, upload, scoring, forms, or analytics

## Publisher philosophy

- The publisher is not a volume engine — it produces **release-eligible reference units**
- SEO is semantic clarification after thesis, claim scope, and source scope are defined — not keyword inflation
- Use pass/fail gates only — no numeric quality scores or grades

## Required before any future publisher output

- Candidate registry, blueprint alignment, content quality, claim/source traceability
- Route/link integrity, technical quality, interface and security/privacy boundaries
- Forbidden language check, `validate_all.py` PASS, audit record, governance approval

## Agent boundary

Automation may produce **candidates**. Governance decides what becomes public.
